<title type="html"><![CDATA[multiple power bars]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=133&amp;p=828#p828"><![CDATA[
The solid part of the bar is obvious enough (update the nametable).  If you want one energy unit per pixel, it'd be: energy / 8 = number of solid blocks.  The remainder would be the number of pixels filled in the partial block.<br /><br />Either sprites or background could be used for the partial blocks.  The sprite version would be a solid block partially hidden beneath the 'previous' solid BG block (this is like the trick I used for the blood lines in my old Halloween demo), and the all-background version would require background tiles for all 8 partial stages.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Mon Jan 03, 2005 6:25 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
